* Well, she'd got his attention at least.
Iris backed up towards the CF, rifle shouldered and ready to fire again.
By now Prowl had noticed her and was charging, her mind quickly going over 
her armory to see if there was something that could do a better job then the 
gun.
There was nothing.*

" Slag!"

* Firing off rapidly she aimed all she had at Prowl as he came closer, 
backing up towards the CF all the time.

From across the field IR saw the large form of Prowl moving towards the 
base, glancing over to see him moving towards a red armored transformer.
But that person looked familier so she stopped chargeing at Demon Wulf and 
narrowed her eyes.
Who...Iris!
< PROWL! NO!> She was trying to reach him with her mind, starting off 
towards him to try and get between his teeth and Iris.
< Stop! Stop!>
Why couldn't he listen?!
She was at a full run, but even that couldn't save her friend from the 
monster that was moving towards her. IR already knew too late that she 
wouldn't reach her in time.
But maybe she could stop Prowl another way, with the time.
Linking with his she imagined a very high pitched sound, so high that it 
made her internal systems rattle, hoping that it was enough to destract him 
enough to slow him down.*
